<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 4. Amphicteis hwanghaiensis sp. nov. (paratype) A anterior end, dorsal view B anterior end C thoracic parapodia. Numbers refer to segments; bII-V = branchiae, segments II-V, respectively; P = prostomium; * = middle lobe of prostomium; Pe = peristomium." , "Figure 3. Amphicteis hwanghaiensis sp. nov. (holotype) A limbate capillary notochaeta B notochaetae C paleae D thoracic uncini, arrows point to subrostal process E abdominal uncini, arrows point to subrostal process." , "Figure 2. Amphicteis hwanghaiensis sp. nov. (holotype) A prostomium, dorsal view B position of branchiae, dorsal view C paleae D thoracic parapodium E limbate capillary notochaeta F abdominal parapodium G thoracic uncinus H abdominal uncinus. Scale bars: 500 µm (A, B, D, F); 250 µm (C); 100 µm (E); 10 µm (G, H)." , "Figure 1. Amphicteis hwanghaiensis sp. nov. (holotype) A anterior end, dorsal view B anterior end, lateral view C anterior end, ventral view D branchiae E anterior end F thoracic parapodia, arrows point to notopodial cirri G abdominal parapodia, arrows point to notopodial (large) and neuropodial (small) cirri H posterior end, ventral view. Numbers refer to segments; ll = lower lip, bII-V = branchiae, segments II-V, respectively." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/472507" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/472506" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/472505" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/472504" .

